column5: Had the past week off for a vaction, spent 5 days north of Napanee on Beaver lake which was cut short when i wiped out the bottom end off my motor, spent the remander of it fishing at home with some buddy"s , eries on fire right now with lots of 5 and 6 pounders being caught.
Nice Wayne !   Maybe you did crack that other boat...
ya i wish i had Wayne at least maybe the insurance would have covered it then LOL! I can,t complain in all my years of fishing i have never hit before, luck had to run out sooner or later LOL!
That looks prepped for a Bob's nose cone
It happens to the best of em Wayne.  Nice going on the week.  At least it happened on the last day not the first.  Cheers buddy!!  Edit: Typo
I think you may have water in your lower unit oil bud !
LMAO you think! Ya in the marina right now for a Quote for insurance, looking to be around $5500 for a complete new lower gear case, and yes i am covered for this one lol!
Ouch!!!!  I can relate to the sickening feeling in the gut, when ya hear the thud But you really got some beauty hawgs to show  for it
